# PowerShell Coding Standards

## _deploy.ps1 File Standard

Every deployable script folder should include a `_deploy.ps1` that uses a deployment handler module:

```powershell
Import-Module Deploy-Handler -Force -ErrorAction Stop
Deploy-Files -FromFolder $PSScriptRoot -ComputerNameList @("*-db", "*-app")
```

**Rules:**
- Always use `Import-Module Deploy-Handler -Force -ErrorAction Stop`
- Always use `Deploy-Files -FromFolder $PSScriptRoot`
- If recipient computers unknown, skip `-ComputerNameList`

## Deployment Execution Rules

**The agent must NEVER run deployment commands autonomously.**

When the user explicitly requests deployment:
1. Look for `_deploy.ps1` in the **same folder** as the script being worked on
2. If the file exists, run it: `pwsh -NoProfile -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File ".\_deploy.ps1"`
3. If the file does NOT exist, inform the user and do NOT attempt deployment

**What `_deploy.ps1` handles automatically:**
- Code signing of all scripts
- Distribution to target servers
- Archiving of files
- Deployment of ALL modules used by the script

**Do NOT deploy when:**
- User did not explicitly request deployment
- Just making code fixes or changes

## Module Import Standards

**For .ps1 scripts:**
```powershell
Import-Module GlobalFunctions -Force
```

## Parameter Type Rules

**Switch Parameters:** Use `-Name` (enable) or `-Name:$false` (disable)
- NEVER use `-Name $true`

**Boolean Parameters:** Use `-Name:$true` or `-Name:$false`
- NEVER use bare `-Name`

**Resolve types:**
```powershell
(Get-Command <cmd>)?.Parameters['Param']?.ParameterType
```

## String Interpolation

Always wrap variable names in subexpressions when followed by punctuation:
```powershell
"X: $($varName): Y"    # Correct
"X: $varName: Y"       # Wrong
```

## Logging Standards

Use `Write-LogMessage` from GlobalFunctions:
```powershell
Write-LogMessage "Test message" -Level INFO
Write-LogMessage "Warning" -Level WARN
Write-LogMessage "Error" -Level ERROR -Exception $_
```

**Rules:**
- Do NOT enclose the level with quotes
- Always add `-Exception $_` in catch statements

## IIS Management

**Always use `appcmd.exe` for IIS configuration.**

The WebAdministration module is not available or does not work in PowerShell 7.

```powershell
$appcmd = "$env:SystemRoot\System32\inetsrv\appcmd.exe"
& $appcmd list apppool /name:MyAppPool
& $appcmd add apppool /name:MyAppPool
& $appcmd set config MySite /section:windowsAuthentication /enabled:true
```

## Remoting Restrictions

**NO remoting is allowed to servers.**

Do NOT use:
- `Invoke-Command -ComputerName`
- `Enter-PSSession`
- `New-PSSession`
- WinRM/PSRemoting
- Any remote execution methods

All scripts must run locally on the target server via deployment (`_deploy.ps1`).
